parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, such as headlights, taillights, and instrument cluster, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights
taillights
or instrument cluster not functioning
fog lights staying on
battery draining
and power door locks malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
clutch pedal not returning to its normal position
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Ignition key not staying in place
vehicle not starting
and battery draining.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Interior Lighting and Instrument Cluster Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior lighting and instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose visibility of critical information, leading to accidents or errors.
symptoms: Instrument cluster not illuminating
speedometer and gauges not functioning
and interior lights not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the subframe can cause the front end of the vehicle to collapse, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle collapses
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle makes popping noises when starting from a dead stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause sharp edges and pieces to fall into the air vent, potentially causing injury in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The dashboard cracks
pieces of the dashboard fall into the air vent
the dashboard cracks in multiple places
the dashboard crumbling and falling apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension and Steering Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of front suspension and steering components can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates
the front tires wear unevenly
the vehicle makes a grinding or rubbing noise when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights or fog lights fail to turn off
the horn fails to work
the airbag light comes on
the dashboard lights or warning lights fail to illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and brake systems can cause accidents, loss of control, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the brakes make a grinding or squealing noise
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.
